==English==

===Adverbial phrase===
'''[[not]] [[at]] [[all]]'''

# (''emphatically'') [[Not]].
#:''He's '''not at all''' friendly towards his ex-wife.''
# {{idiom}} Used as a conventional reply to an expression of gratitude.

====Synonyms====
*(''emphatically: not''): [[by no means]], [[hardly]], [[in no way]], [[not in the least]], [[not in the slightest]], [[not the least bit]], [[not the slightest bit]]
*(''conventional reply to expression of gratitude''): [[don't mention it]], [[forget it]], [[it's nothing]], [[no problem]], [[that's all right]], [[that's OK]], [[think nothing of it]], [[you're welcome]]

